Message.MsgText: HMGR0235=HMGR0235W: The core group member {0} reported a problem. The member reporting the problem logged the reason using message {1}.
Message.Explanation: This process received a message that another core group member has reported a problem.
Message.UserResponse: For more information, locate the specified message ID in the log file for the core group member that reported the problem. If necessary, stop or terminate the failing process.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0234=HMGR0234W: The active coordinator detected that the state rebuild operation did not complete within the expected time. Waiting for state messages from the following process set: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The active coordinator was in the process of rebuilding state, but did not receive the expected state messages from all core group processes within the expected time limit.
Message.UserResponse: Review the log files for the specified set of processes that failed to send state messages to determine the problem. If necessary, stop or terminate the failing processes.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0233=HMGR0233E: The active coordinator received a message from {0} with inconsistent {1} state for subject {2}, the post contents were {3} with {4} existing state.
Message.Explanation: An internal inconsistency was detected. The active coordinator ignores the incoming message.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0232=HMGR0232E: The active coordinator received a message from {0} indicating this process is a core group bridge; however, there are no core group bridges {1}.
Message.Explanation: An internal inconsistency was detected. The active coordinator ignores the incoming message.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0231=HMGR0231W: The active coordinator detected a unexpected condition while processing the {0} component of a message with {1} mode from {2}, a {3} was expected. Current state is {4}.
Message.Explanation: This is an indication of internal state mismatch between coregroup members and should not frequently occur, the message is ignored by the active coordinator.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0230=HMGR0230E: Core group bridge ownership of subject {0} is in contention between bridges {1}.
Message.Explanation: An internal inconsistency was detected.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1310=HMGR1310E: The MBean operation did not complete within {0} seconds.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager did not receive a response to a MBean operation within the time limit set for a JMX command.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the failing command. If the problem persists, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0229=HMGR0229I: A new data stack view has been installed. The view identifier is {0}. The data stack name is {1} and the number of members in the new view is {2}.
Message.Explanation: Processes have been added or removed from the existing view.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0228=HMGR0228I: The Coordinator is not an Active Coordinator for core group {0}. The active coordinator set is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The coordinator in this process is not an active coordinator for the specified core group.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0227=HMGR0227E: The request to create a Core Group Bridge on this server has failed. The request is invalid.
Message.Explanation: A core group bridge can only be created on a server that is part of a network deployment configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Create the core group bridge on an eligible server.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0226=HMGR0226I: The core stack configuration parameter {0} has been set to {1}.
Message.Explanation: A core stack custom property was used to override the default value for the specified configuration parameter.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0225=HMGR0225E: A parsing error occurred for core group custom property {0}. The value is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The specified value is not valid for this custom property.
Message.UserResponse: See the product documentation to determine the values that can be specified for this custom property.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0224=HMGR0224E: The core group custom property {0} is out of range. Value {1} is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: The specified value is not valid for this custom property.
Message.UserResponse: See the product documentation to determine the values that can be specified for this custom property.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0223=HMGR0223W: An unrecoverable error has occurred on the DCS core stack for core group {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An error was received from the DCS transport channel.
Message.UserResponse: If the error does not resolve itself, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0222=HMGR0222W: A request to move the active member of a group from one server to another cannot be performed. The group is not stable. The group is {0}
Message.Explanation: The high availability group is currently undergoing a state transition that cannot be interrupted.
Message.UserResponse: Wait for the transition to complete and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0221=HMGR0221W: A request to activate or deactivate a member cannot be performed. The requested state is {0}, the member identifier is {1} and the group is {2}
Message.Explanation: The specified member could not be activated or deactivated because it is already in that state.
Message.UserResponse: If you need to deactivate a member, select a member that is in the active state, and retry the operation. If you need to activate a member, select a member that is in the inactive state, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0220=HMGR0220W: A request to move the active member of a group from one server to another cannot be performed. One of the members does not exist. The member identifier is {0} and the group is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The identified member was not moved because it is not a member of the specified core group.
Message.UserResponse: Select a member that is defined as a member of this core group, and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1309=HMGR1309E: The group name string is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The specified high availability group name must be either a comma delimited string of name=value pairs, or an asterisk character.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a valid group name, a valid subset of a group name, or an asterisk character, and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1308=HMGR1308E: An unexpected failure occurred.
Message.Explanation: During processing of a high availability manager MBean, an unexpected error condition occurred.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the failing command. If the problem persists, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1307=HMGR1307E: The member {0} is not in {1} state.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager MBean operation cannot be performed because the indicated member is not in the required state.
Message.UserResponse: Either wait for the member to reach the required state, and then retry this command, or specify a different high availability group member when you issue the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1306=HMGR1306E: The specified member {0} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The specified Node and ServerName parameters do not match any existing high availability group members.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a valid member and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1305=HMGR1305E: The specified group does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The name specified for the GroupName parameter does not match any existing high availability groups.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a valid high availability group name for the GroupName parameter, and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1304=HMGR1304E: The GroupName parameter must specify a group governed by a {0} policy.
Message.Explanation: The policy for the specified high availability group is not of the required type.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the name of a high availability group that is associated with the indicated policy type as the value for the GroupName parameter, and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1303=HMGR1303E: A send message problem has occurred.
Message.Explanation: A problem has occurred while attempting to send a message to the active coordinator.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the command. If the problem persists, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1302=HMGR1302E: View is changing. Retry command after the view has stabilized.
Message.Explanation: A high availability manager MBean operation could not be completed because the view is changing. The view might be changing because servers are being started, or servers have been stopped or have failed.
Message.UserResponse: Wait for the core group view to stabilize and then retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1301=HMGR1301E: No active coordinators for core group {0} could be found.
Message.Explanation: A high availability manager MBean operation could not be completed because no active coordinator could be found for the core group.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that at least two of the servers that are members of this core group are running. If two servers are running, check their messages log files for additional messages that might indicate a problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1300=HMGR1300E: {0} parameter is null.
Message.Explanation: A high availability manager MBean operation detected a null parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Check the product documentation for the correct settings for the specified paramenter, and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0219=HMGR0219I: An unrecognized view change event was received from the DCS transport. The view identifier is {0} and the event is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The type of the event is not recognized. The high availability manager could not respond to the view change event that it received from the DCS transport because it did not recognize the specified event type.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0218=HMGR0218I: A new core group view has been installed. The core group is {0}. The view identifier is {1}. The number of members in the new view is {2}.
Message.Explanation: Processes have been added or removed from the existing view.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0213=HMGR0213E: A request to activate or deactivate a group member was made while the policy was unstable. The GroupName is {0} The policy type is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager detected an internal inconsistency.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0212=HMGR0212I: A request to remove the group member for server {0} from the group state aggregion for group name {1} cannot be honored. The group does not currently exist.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager detected an internal inconsistency.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0211=HMGR0211E: Unable to create the group state aggregation object on the active coordinator for group {0} in response to a group join from server {1}. The policy for the group cannot be determined. The exception is {2}
Message.Explanation: The policy for the specified high availability group cannot be found on the server. However, the policy was available on the server when the join was done.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0210=HMGR0210I: Unable to run the policy for group {0}. The group may have been deleted.
Message.Explanation: In response to a change in the state of a high availability group, the high availability manager tried to apply the policy for that group. The policy could not be applied because the high availability group currently has no members, and might have been deleted.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0209=HMGR0209E: An internal error occured while processing the policy for group {0}. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager detected an internal logic error. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0208=HMGR0208E: The Coordinator could not process a message. The coordinator is in FAILED state. The message is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has detected an internal logic error.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0207=HMGR0207I: The Coordinator was previously an Active Coordinator for core group {0} but has lost leadership. The active coordinator set is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The coordinator in this process is no longer an active coordinator.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0206=HMGR0206I: The Coordinator is an Active Coordinator for core group {0}. The active coordinator set is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The coordinator in this process has been elected as an active coordinator.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0205=HMGR0205E: The Coordinator could not process a message. The state and the message are inconstent. The state is {0} and the message is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has detected an internal logic error.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0204=HMGR0204E: The Coordinator could not process a message. The message is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has detected an internal logic error.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0203=HMGR0203E: The active Coordinator was found to be in an invalid state and could not process a message. The state is {0}, the message is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has detected an internal logic error.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0201=HMGR0201E: A communication exception occured while sending a message. The message type is {0}. The GroupName is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt to send a message failed with a exception in the communication stack. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. Ensure that all network communications are operating properly. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR3002=HMGR3002E: An unexpected condition was encountered during this admin task. The class is {0}, the method is {1} and internal details {2}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected internal error occurred. See the description of the specified exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR3001=HMGR3001E: A failure occured while removing server {0} on node {1} from core group {2}. The exception is {3}.
Message.Explanation: The specified server was not removed from the indicated core group. See the exception stack trace for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem and retry the operation. If the root cause cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR3000=HMGR3000E: A failure occured while adding server {0} on node {1} to core group {2}. The exception is {3}.
Message.Explanation: The specified server was not added to the indicated core group. See the exception stack trace for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem and retry the operation. If the root cause cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0099=HMGR0099E: This process received an updated configuration document from the {0} and it is no longer a member of core group {1}.
Message.Explanation: This process was given an updated configuration document and it was removed from the core group it was started in.
Message.UserResponse: Synchronize the nodeagent that this process is located on with the deployment manager. After synchronization, restart this process.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0098=HMGR0098E: Unable to obtain a reference to the admin service.
Message.Explanation: Unable to obtain a reference to the admin service.
Message.UserResponse: Contact IBM Service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0097=HMGR0097E: Unknown error was encountered when trying to push configuration to core group {0}. See exception for more information. Exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: An unknown error was encountered when trying to push configuration to a core group member, the core group did not receive new configuration data.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, contact IBM service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0096=HMGR0096E: An error was encountered when trying to pull configuration from Deployment Manager. See exception for more information. Exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: An error was encountered when trying to pull configuration from the Deployment Manager, this process may be running on old configuration data.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, contact IBM service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0095=HMGR0095I: Unable to locate any running processes for core group {0} that are not in single server mode. Core group configuration was not updated dynamically.
Message.Explanation: The Deployment Manager was unable to locate any HAManager MBeans on a process that is not running in single server mode for the specified core group.
Message.UserResponse: Ignore this message if there are no running processes, or if all running processes are in single server mode. Otherwise ensure that node agents are running when performing configuration changes.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0094=HMGR0094E: The query for MBean {0} failed.
Message.Explanation: Malformed ObjectName exception encountered.
Message.UserResponse: Contact IBM Service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0093=HMGR0093E: Unable to create an Admin Client connection to the deployment manager. Exception: {0}.
Message.Explanation: Unable to create an Admin Client connection to the deployment manager.
Message.UserResponse: Contact IBM Service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0092=HMGR0092W: Unable to get HA Manager MBean on the Deployment Manager, object name used for query is {0}.
Message.Explanation: Unable to get the HA Manager MBean on the Deployment Manager.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the Deployment Manager is running, otherwise contact IBM Service.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0091=HMGR0091I: An outdated core group configuration was read from the repository. The current configuration is {0}. The configuration just read is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The core group configuration might not have been updated correctly.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0090=HMGR0090W: An attempt to update the High Availability manager configuration has failed. The required documents are not available on this node.
Message.Explanation: The core group configuration could not be updated correctly.
Message.UserResponse: Manually synchronize the configuration from the master repository on the deployment manager. Application servers on the affected node might need to be recycled.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0089=HMGR0089E: A configuration available message could not be delivered. The configuration version is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The core group configuration could not be updated correctly.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0088=HMGR0088I: HA Policy information from the new core group configuration was not applied. There were {0} errors in the new configuration.
Message.Explanation: Policy errors are tolerated when the configuration is read, but these errors prevent policy information from being updated.
Message.UserResponse: Scan the SystemOut.log file for information related to the parsing errors and correct the errors.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0087=HMGR0087I: An unrecoverable error was encountered while merging the core group configuration. The version is {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager encountered an unrecoverable error while updating the core group configuration settings.
Message.UserResponse: Synchronize the configuration to the node in question, then restart the server. If synchronizing the configuration does not solve the problem, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for additional help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0086=HMGR0086I: This server is updating its core group configuration. The new document version is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The core group document is being updated.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0085=HMGR0085I: This server received a message that a new core group document is available. This server is already running on that document version.
Message.Explanation: The server is already using the new core group document.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0083=HMGR0083E: An error was encountered merging configuration information. The element type is {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The coregroup.xml configuration document contains a syntax error or has been corrupted.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0081=HMGR0081E: An error was received while reloading a configuration document. The document name is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified configuration document has an unknown problem.
Message.UserResponse: Scan the SystemOut.log file for error messages relating to failures in loading this configuration document. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for additional help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0080=HMGR0080E: Unable to obtain a reference to the ConfigRepository. Configuration documents cannot be updated dynamically.
Message.Explanation: An unknown problem exists with the ConfigRepository management bean definition table.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0071=HMGR0071E: The coreGroupName attribute in the HAManagerService is null.
Message.Explanation: The coreGroupName attribute must be set to the core group with which this server is associated. Null is not allowed.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0070=HMGR0070E: An error was encountered while processing the hamanagerservice.xml document. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The hamanagerservice.xml configuration document contains a syntax error or has been corrupted.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0503=HMGR0503I: The message path of the internal data stack named {0} is highly congested.
Message.Explanation: The message path of the internal data stack that is used by the partitioned managed group has reached its upper congestion limit.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0502=HMGR0502E: An error occurred while using the internal data stack named {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager detected problem with the internal data stack that is used by the partitioned managed group. See the exception stack trace for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem. If the root cause cannot be determined and corrected, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0501=HMGR0501E: Encountered an abnormal termination of the internal data stack named {0}.
Message.Explanation: The internal data stack of the view synchronous high-availability manager group encountered an unexpected termination event. See the exception stack trace for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem. If the root cause cannot be determined and corrected, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0064=HMGR0064W: Resolution of IP Addresses for host name {0} found only the loopback address. The loopback address will be used.
Message.Explanation: There might be a problem with the host name or domain name service (DNS) name resolution. Under normal circumstances, a non-loopback address is expected.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the host name or the DNS name resolution problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0063=HMGR0063W: The DCS_UNICAST_ADDRESS end point for server {0} on node {1} has an invalid value. {2} Will be used instead.
Message.Explanation: A null or empty string was found. Valid values include the host name, a textual IP address, or *.
Message.UserResponse: Enter the proper host name in the DCS_UNICAST_ADDRESS field.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0062=HMGR0062I: A DCS_UNICAST_ADDRESS end point does not exist for server {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: This end point is required and should be allocated when the process is created.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0061=HMGR0061E: An error was encountered while processing the coregroup. The entry for server {0}, node {1} failed. The exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An incorrect server entry exists in the core group configuration document.
Message.UserResponse: See the description of the specified exception for more information about what caused the problem, and correct the problem. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for additional help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0060=HMGR0060W: An error was encountered while obtaining the host and port information for server {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: The serverindex.xml file for the specified node appears to be out of date.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem does not resolve itself, perform a full resynchronize from the master repository.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0049=HMGR0049E: A duplicate policy name was found in the configuration data. The policy name is {0}.
Message.Explanation: Two policy definitions were found that have the same name. Each policy definition must have a unique name.
Message.UserResponse: Assign a different name to one of the policies. This name must be unique from any other policy name.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0048=HMGR0048E: A failure occurred while attempting to create a default HAManager policy. The name of the policy is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An internal initialization error occurred. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Look for previous messages in the SystemOut.log file that contain initialization failure information. If, after analyzing these messages, you cannot determine the cause of the export problem,See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for additional help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0047=HMGR0047E: An error occured while processing the policy configuration information. The specified PolicyFactory class {0} was not instantiable. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: The name of the policy factory specified in the configuration data is incorrect.
Message.UserResponse: Either the policy factory name is entered incorrectly or that policy factory class is not available on this server. Determine which of these situations has occurred, and correct the problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0046=HMGR0046E: An error occured while processing the policy configuration information. The specified PolicyFactory class {0} is not a PolicyFactory.
Message.Explanation: The name of the policy factory specified in the configuration data is incorrect.
Message.UserResponse: Enter a valid name for the policy factory class.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0045=HMGR0045W: The server list for policy {0} is empty. This policy requires at least one server.
Message.Explanation: The server list for the specified policy is empty.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the configuration state.

Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0159=HMGR0159E: An attempt to administratively enable High Availability Group {0} failed because the member is not in the disabled state. The current member state is {1}.
Message.Explanation: A member of the specified core group is not in the disabled state.
Message.UserResponse: Check the current state of the members of the specified core group, and determine which member is not in the disabled state.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0158=HMGR0158E: The attempt to power down suspect server {0} failed.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has determined that the specified server, which is hosting a member of a critical cluster, has failed. An attempt to shutdown this server to allow safe failover has failed.
Message.UserResponse: Try to determine why the server failed. If possible, fix the problem and start the server again so that it can rejoin the cluster.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0157=HMGR0157E: The channel chain {0} has failed to start after {1} retries. The process will be terminated.
Message.Explanation: The DCS transport channel failed to start. The port that is designated for the DCS transport channel is probably not available. This situation can occur if the process was previously terminated abnormally.
Message.UserResponse: Wait for the operating system to release the port and restart the process. You should also check the SystemOut.log file for other channel transport chain related messages.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0152=HMGR0152W: CPU Starvation detected. Current thread scheduling delay is {0} seconds.
Message.Explanation: Threads are not being dispatched in a timely manner, and this may affect system stability.
Message.UserResponse: Thread scheduling delays can have many different causes. High CPU utilization or low memory resulting in long garbage collection times or paging to disk are possibilities. Perform resource analysis to determine the proper course of action. This message will disappear when the thread scheduling delay has been corrected.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0151=HMGR0151E: A problem was encountered while updating the core group member list. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The core group member list could not be dynamically updated.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0150=HMGR0150E: An attempt to create a token to secure the High Availability Manager connection failed. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected internal error has occurred. See the description of the specified exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0149=HMGR0149E: An attempt to open a connection to core group {0} has been rejected. The sending process has a name of {1} and an IP address of {2}. Global security in the local process is {3}. Global security in the sending process is {4}. The received token starts with {5}. The exception is {6}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has rejected a connection attempt.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that global security is either enabled on both processes or disabled on both processes, and ensure that both the sending and receiving processes are members of the same core group.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0148=HMGR0148I: The channel chain transport for core group {0} contains an SSL channel.
Message.Explanation: The specified core group is using a secure transport chain.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0147=HMGR0147E: An error was encountered during liveness checking. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager encountered an error while verifying that core group members are alive. Further verification will not occur and failover processing might not function properly.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0146=HMGR0146W: Group {0} is not scheduled for liveness checking.
Message.Explanation: An internal inconsistency was detected. This inconsistency might affect failover for the indicated group.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0145=HMGR0145W: The cluster {0} is now critical.
Message.Explanation: This specified cluster is currently online but the loss of one more cluster members will cause it to terminate.
Message.UserResponse: Bring one or more of the other cluster members online or use the administrative console to remove the offline cluster members from the cluster. Lowering the number of servers that are part of the cluster lowers the number of cluster members that must remain active in order to achieve quorum.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0144=HMGR0144I: Powering down suspect server {0}
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager has determined that the specified server, which is hosting a member of a critical cluster, has failed. The server is being shutdown to allow safe failover.
Message.UserResponse: Check the server to determine why it failed. If you can fix the problem, start the server again so it can rejoin the cluster.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0143=HMGR0143E: An error occurred when the High Availability Manager attempted to dispatch a thread. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: An unrecoverable thread dispatch error occurred.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0142=HMGR0142E: An error occurred in a component called back by the High Availability Manager. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The called component did not detect that an error occurred.
Message.UserResponse: Use the stack trace to determine which component failed, and perform diagnostics for that component. For additional help in determining why the component failed, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0141=HMGR0141E: Sending local state information to an active coordinator failed. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The group state could not be synchronized correctly.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem does not resolve by itself, stop the server and then start the server again. If the problem still exists, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0140=HMGR0140E: An event indicating that the core group membership is inconsistent was received. Recovery failed. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The core group membership could not be updated correctly.
Message.UserResponse: Synchronize the configuration to the node in question, then restart the server. If synchronizing the configuration does not solve the problem, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1228=HMGR1228W: The Administrative request could not be completed because the specified member or group is not in the correct state. The request is "{0}", the member is "{1}" and the group name is "{2}". Reason = "{3}".
Message.Explanation: An asynchronous administrative operation was requested, and during background processing, it was determined that the specified high availability member or high availability group is not in the correct state for the requested action. Therefore, no action was taken.
Message.UserResponse: Because of the timing of asynchronous operations, it is normal for the high availability manager to occasionally encounter this situation. Verify that the current state of the high availability member or high availability group, and if necessary, retry the command that failed.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1227=HMGR1227W: The Administrative request could not be completed because the core group membership is not stable. The request is "{0}", the member is "{1}" and the group name is "{2}".
Message.Explanation: An asynchronous administrative operation was requested, and during background processing, the high availability manager determined that the core group membership is changing. Therefore, no action was taken.
Message.UserResponse: Because of the timing of asynchronous operations, it is normal for the high availability manager to occasionally encounter this situation. Wait for the servers in this core group to enter a steady state (are either in a started or stopped state) and retry the command that failed.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1226=HMGR1226W: The Administrative request could not be completed because the specified member does not exist. The request is "{0}" the member is "{1}", the group is "{2}"
Message.Explanation: An asynchronous administrative operation was requested, and during background processing, the specified high availability group member could not be found. Therefore, no action was taken.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the failing command with valid NodeName and ServerName parameters.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1225=HMGR1225W: The Administrative request could not be completed because the specified group does not exist. The request is "{0}" and the group name is "{1}".
Message.Explanation: An asynchronous administrative operation was requested, and during background processing, the specified high availability group could not be found. Therefore, no action was taken.
Message.UserResponse: Retry the failing command with a valid GroupName parameter.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0139=HMGR0139I: A non-core stack event has been routed to the core stack. The event is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The core stack received an event that is not a core stack event. The specified event is ignored.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0138=HMGR0138I: Terminate has been called on a core stack. The core stack {0} will be terminated.
Message.Explanation: The specified core stack has been shut down.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0137=HMGR0137I: Terminate has been called on the default core stack. This is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: Only the high availability manager can terminate the default core group stack.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0136=HMGR0136I: No such cluster defined {0}
Message.Explanation: This happens because if a cluster is added then its definition is pushed asynchronously to all nodes. Some nodes might not know about a cluster when other do as a result. This problem will correct itself in a few seconds.
Message.UserResponse: If this persists do a manual nodesync on the problem nodes, if this fails then see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0135=HMGR0135I: Cluster {0} has quorum.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster has quorum.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0134=HMGR0134I: Cluster {0} is waiting for quorum. Currently {1} members online. At least {2} votes of {3} votes required for quorum.
Message.Explanation: The cluster has services which cannot activate without the cluster having quorum. Normally, each server has a single vote and the majority of the servers must be online for quorum. If the number of servers is even then the first server has two votes.
Message.UserResponse: Start more cluster members to achieve quorum.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0133=HMGR0133E: Exception constructing cluster {0}, exception {1}
Message.Explanation: Quorum is enabled for an unknown cluster.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0132=HMGR0132I: The local member of group {0} failed to respond properly to a health check. The exception is {1}. The JVM will be terminated.
Message.Explanation: The JVM is being terminated because the local member of the specified group is no longer functioning properly.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0131=HMGR0131I: The local member of group {0} has not responded to a health check. The JVM will be terminated.
Message.Explanation: The JVM is being terminated because the local member of the specified group is no longer functioning properly.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0130=HMGR0130I: The local member of group {0} has indicated that is it not alive. The JVM will be terminated. This server was shut down to prevent damage and maintain high availability in this cluster. Address any exceptions from this member. After the server restarts, the member is rejoined to the group.
Message.Explanation: The JVM is being terminated because the local member of the specified group is no longer functioning properly.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0129=HMGR0129I: The local member of group {0} has been disabled. The reason is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The local member of the specified core group was disabled at your request.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0128=HMGR0128E: The wrong context object was passed on a callback to the AsynchOperationComplete interface. The method is {0}, the group is {1}, the context object is {2} and the expected context is {3}.
Message.Explanation: The specified programming error was detected.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0127=HMGR0127I: The HA Manager has discarded a request to activate or deactivate a group member. The member is disabled. The group is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The policy for the specified high availability group initiated a request to activate or deactivate a group member. The high availability manager determined that the requested member is disabled.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0126=HMGR0126I: The method {0} has been called on the HAGroup object for group {1}, but the member has already left that group.
Message.Explanation: An unusual condition was detected. This condition might be the result of a programming error.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0125=HMGR0125I: An activate or deactive request for the local member of group {0} failed. The reason is {1}, the data is {2} and the exception is {3}
Message.Explanation: A group member failed to perform the requested action. The group member will be disabled.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0124=HMGR0124I: An activate or deactive request for the local member of group {0} failed. The reason is {1} and the data is {2}
Message.Explanation: A group member failed to perform the requested action. The group member will be disabled.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0123=HMGR0123I: A GroupUpdate message was received for a group that does not exist. The group name is {0}.
Message.Explanation: An unusual situation has occured. This situation might be the result of message latency.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0122=HMGR0122E: An error occurred sending a DCS Multicast message. The message type is {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred. See the exception stack trace for more detail.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem. If the root cause cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0121=HMGR0121E: An error occurred sending a DCS Unicast message. The target member is {0}. The message type is {1}. The exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred. See the exception stack trace for more detail.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem. If the root cause cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0120=HMGR0120E: An error occurred processing a callback from DCS. The method is {0}. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred. See the exception stack trace for more detail.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the root cause of the problem. If the root cause cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1203=HMGR1203I: HA Manager administrative action requested. Operation is "{0}", current active member is "{1}", requested active member is "{2}", the group is "{3}".
Message.Explanation: The specified high availability manager administrative action was requested.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1202=HMGR1202I: HA Manager administrative action requested. Operation is "{0}", the member is "{1}", the group is "{2}".
Message.Explanation: The specified high availability manager administrative action was requested.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1201=HMGR1201I: HA Manager administrative action requested. Operation is "{0}", the group is "{1}".
Message.Explanation: The specified high availability manager administrative action was requested.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1200=HMGR1200I: HA Manager administrative action requested. Operation is "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The specified high availability manager administrative action was requested.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0119=HMGR0119I: The GMS service has requested that the server be terminated. The reason is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The Group Membership Service (GMS) requested termination. The GMS should have logged the reason for this request.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0117=HMGR0117E: Quorum on group {0} with members {1} has been lost and the process contains active HA Group members. The process must be terminated.
Message.Explanation: A cluster member that contains quorum sensitive groups has lost quorum but has active members. The process must be terminated.
Message.UserResponse: Restart the failed servers or correct the network partition.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0114=HMGR0114E: An unexpected error occurred while forwarding group change information to the active coordinator. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be sent because of an unrecoverable error.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0113=HMGR0113E: A communication error occurred while forwarding group change information to the active coordinator. The exception is {0}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be sent because of a failure in the communication stack.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0112=HMGR0112E: An unexpected error occurred during object Serialization. The object class is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected internal error occurred. See the description of the specified exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0111=HMGR0111E: An unexpected internal error occured during a joinGroup operation. The GroupName is {0}, the instance is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected internal error occurred. See the description of the specified exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the cause of the exception. If the root cause of the problem cannot be determined, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0109=HMGR0109E: An unexpected exception was encountered while the HAManager was processing a callback from a using program. The class is {0}, the method is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: A problem occurred while processing an application callback.
Message.UserResponse: A programming error by a high availability manager user is probably the cause of this problem. Use the information in the message to find and correct the root cause of the problem. If you cannot determine the root cause of the problem, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0108=HMGR0108E: An unexpected internal state was encountered. The class is {0}, the method is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An inconsistent internal state was detected.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0107=HMGR0107E: An attempt to activate or deactivate a member failed. An internal failure has occurred. The group is {0} and the exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An inconsistent internal state was detected.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0105=HMGR0105E: An attempt to activate or deactivate a member failed. There local member was not in the proper state. The group is {0}. The local member is {1} and the current state is {2}. The execution stack is {3}
Message.Explanation: An inconsistent internal state was detected.
Message.UserResponse: The root cause of the problem appears to be an internal error. See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0103=HMGR0103I: An attempt to activate or deactivate a member failed. There are no local group members for group {0}.
Message.Explanation: An activate or deactivate message was received but there are no local members in the group to activate or deactivate. This situation can occur under normal conditions, depending on the timing of messages. For example when members are leaving a group, one of them could receive an activate message that was sent just before that member left.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0408=HMGR0408E: The synchronous data stack {0} encountered an unexpected exception processing method {1}. The exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected synchronous data stack exception occurred. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0407=HMGR0407E: A request data command on synchronous data stack {0} failed. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred attempting to peform a synchronous request for data. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0406=HMGR0406E: The data stack {0} encountered an unexpected exception calling method {1}. The exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected data stack exception occurred. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0405=HMGR0405E: The data stack {0} detected an unknown event. The unrecognized event is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager encountered an unknown data stack event. No harm was caused by this condition.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0404=HMGR0404E: The data stack {0} could not process a received message. The message is {1} and the exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager encountered a problem while trying to process a received data stack message. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0403=HMGR0403E: Data stack {0} invoked the call back method {1} and it failed. The exception is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The data stack implementation detected a failure invoking a method on the registered call back class. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Use the associated exception name, message and stack trace to determine the root cause of the failure. If the root cause is an application error, correct the cause of the failure and retry the operation. If the root cause is an internal error, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0402=HMGR0402E: Sending a message on the data stack {0} failed. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred attempting to send a data stack message. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR0401=HMGR0401E: Creation of data stack {0} failed. The exception is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected error occurred while creating the data stack. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1019=HMGR1019W: This process received a message that does not map to an AgentClass channel or to any known Agent channel. The channel name from message is {0}. The sender is {1}. The local AgentClass channel is {2}. The known local Agent Channels are [{3}].
Message.Explanation: A message was sent via the high availability manager Agent framework and received by this member. However, the channel name included in the message does not match any existing AgentClass or Agent channel name. It is possible for this to occur if the receiving component associated with the channel name in the message was removed while the message was in flight.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1018=HMGR1018I: An attempt to cancel creation of a backup Agent has failed. The AgentClass does not have a request scheduled for Agent {0}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager detected the indicated internal inconsistency.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1017=HMGR1017I: An attempt to create a backup Agent has failed. The message could not be delivered to the target. The Agent is {0}.
Message.Explanation: The high availability manager encountered a communication problem while trying to send a message to the target. The high availability manager will try to resend the message.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that all network paths are operating properly.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1016=HMGR1016E: An internal failure occured in an AgentClass. The AgentClass name is {0}. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: An internal failure occured in the specified AgentClass. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1015=HMGR1015E: An internal failure occured in an Agent. The Agent name is {0}. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: An internal failure occured in the specified agent. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: See the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1014=HMGR1014E: A failure occured while processing a membership change for AgentClass {0}. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: There are several reasons why a failure might have occurred while processing a membership change for the specified agent, including application errors, configuration problems and internal errors. See the description of the exception for more information.
Message.UserResponse: Use the associated exception name, message and stack trace to determine the root cause of the failure. If the root cause is an application error or a configuration error, correct the cause of the failure and retry the operation. If the root cause is an internal error, see the problem determination information on the WebSphere Application Server Support Web page, http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support, for help in determining the cause of this problem.

Message.MsgText: HMGR1013=HMGR1013E: A failure occured while processing a membership change for Agent {0}. The exception is {1}
Message.Explanation: There are several reasons why a failure might have occurred while processing a membership change for the specified agent, including application errors, configuration problems and internal errors. See the description of the exception for more information.
